locality (Ktubu) is in 
<collectingCountry box="[681,762,722,748]" name="Yemen" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[775,921,721,748]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh (1958)</bibRefCitation>
recorded other three specimens (all females) from 
<collectingCountry box="[214,292,758,784]" name="Yemen" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[310,381,758,784]" country="Yemen" name="Ad Dali'" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Dhala</collectingRegion>
, Adhramaut and Lauda, north of 
<collectingRegion box="[765,831,758,785]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Aden</collectingRegion>
); recently it has been recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Hawagry, M. S. &amp; Khalil, M. W. &amp; Sharaf, M. R. &amp; Fadl, H. H. &amp; Aldawood, A. S." pageId="15" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref12030" refString="El-Hawagry, M. S., Khalil, M. W., Sharaf, M. R., Fadl, H. H., Aldawood, A. S. (2013) A preliminary study on the insect fauna of Al-Baha Province, Saudi Arabia, with descriptions of two new species. Zookeys, 274, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="2013">
El-Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[1378,1429,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
also from 
<collectingCountry box="[346,492,794,820]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[506,715,794,821]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Al Bahah" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Al-Baha Province</collectingRegion>
). The pronotum of the male is highly distinctive (Fig. 48).
</paragraph>
